        (3) An undertaken given to a court under subsection (1)&#x2014;
        <ol>
        <li>(a) shall be enforceable as if it were an order of the court, and</li>
        <li>(b) shall cease to have effect if, while it is in force, the applicant exercises the power given by section 44(4)(b)(i) to remove the child to other accommodation for a period of more than 24 hours.</li>
        </ol>
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0563P0-03542'>
